Welcome to the clayeditor.com website (the "Site").
The company Plexagon S.r.l. is aware of the importance of the Personal Data of the users of the Site and, therefore, before any use of them, it provides a complete information about their processing and requests the necessary consents. This information is governed by the European Regulation 2016/679, on the protection of personal data (hereinafter, for brevity, "GDPR").
1. Data Controller.
The Data Controller Plexagon S.r.l., based in via Savona 94, Milan 20144. (hereinafter the "Plexagon" or the "Data Controller"). You can always contact the Data Controller by writing to the e-mail address support@clayeditor.com.
2. Type of data collected and purpose of processing
The following Personal Data (hereinafter also referred to as the "Data") will be collected and processed through the Site:
(a) Personal and contact data provided by the user to register with the Site and/or to take advantage of the free trial period;
b) Data related to the image and voice of the subjects filmed in the photographs and/or video footage, uploaded to the Site, in order to enable it to edit the content;
c) Personal data provided for purposes strictly related to the sale, such as purchases and payments, (for example, the e-mail address, personal data, date of birth and password provided to register on the Site and to access the personal account) for any legal purposes arising from the sales contract (such as, accounting, tax and obligations arising from the law);
d) Personal data acquired in case of e-mail contact by the user, in order to acknowledge the user's requests and offer the requested services, assistance and information;
e) Personal data of the user for marketing purposes, i.e. to send promotional offers, advertising material inherent to the services offered to the user, through telematic tools, such as newsletters and e-mails;
f) Personal data for purposes of processing studies and statistical research.
3. Legal basis of the processing
Except for navigation data, regulated by the Cookie Policy, the processing of personal data resides in:
‚óè points 2 (a) (b) (c) in the fulfillment of the contract and the fulfillment of specific legal obligations arising from the contract or for defense in court;
‚óè points 2 (d), in the legitimate interest of the Controller;
‚óè points 2 (e) (f), in any consents given by the user.
4. Period of data retention and methods of data processing
The User's Personal Data are retained, for a period of time not exceeding that necessary to achieve the purposes for which they are processed, subject to the retention periods provided for by law. Specifically:
‚óè Point 2 (a), the Data you provide for registration on the Site, will be retained for a period of time not exceeding 24 months, beginning with the expiration of your subscription or account inactivity for a period of time equal to 24 months.
‚óè Item 2 (b), the Image and Voice Data of the subjects captured in the photographs and/or video footage, will be retained for a period of time not exceeding 24 months
‚óè point 2 (c), Data collected for contractual purposes shall be retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the above purposes and in any case for a period not exceeding 10 years;
‚óè point 2 (d), Data collected for the purpose of providing assistance to you are retained for a period of time not exceeding 24 months from the last communication
‚óè item 2 (e), Data collected for marketing purposes are retained for a period of time not exceeding 2 years
‚óè point 2 (f), Data collected for analytical purposes will be kept for a period of time not exceeding 2 years.
The Data will be processed with mainly computerized and telematic tools and in compliance with confidentiality and security rules provided by law, consequent regulations and specific provisions. Specific security measures are in particular observed to prevent the loss of Data, illegal or incorrect use and unauthorized access.
5. Compulsory or optional nature of the data
With the exception of navigation data (the provision and collection of which is governed by the "Cookie Policy"), the provision to the Data Controller of personal data both to respond to user requests and queries and for marketing purposes and the study of consumption habits and preferences is free, optional and optional.
With regard to the purposes of point 2 (b), (c), (d), the provision of data is necessary for the performance of the services you requested and for the possible conclusion of the sales contract; in fact, the failure to provide certain Data may make it impossible to use the services provided by the Site.
Categories of recipients of personal data
The Data may be known and processed by:
‚óè Employees and consultants of the Data Controller, who will act as authorized entities for the processing;
‚óè Companies that perform for the Data Controller, in the capacity of Data Processors, specific technical and organizational services related to the use of the Site;
‚óè Paddle Payments Limit solely to execute the contract for the purchase of products on the Site;
‚óè Public or private entities with respect to which there is, for the Data Controller, an obligation (or faculty recognized by rule of law or secondary or EU regulations) or a need for communication.
In addition, the Data may be disclosed to law enforcement or judicial authorities, in accordance with the law and upon formal request by such entities, or if there are reasonable grounds to believe that the disclosure of such data is reasonably necessary to (1) investigate, prevent, or take action regarding suspected unlawful activities or assist state control and supervisory authorities; (2) defend against any claims or allegations from third parties, or protect the security of its Site and the Owner (3) exercise or protect the rights, property or safety of Plexagon and its customers, employees or any other person.
6. Transfer outside the EU
Your Data will not be disseminated. Your Data may be transferred to countries outside the EU. The transfer will take place in compliance with applicable legislation and by taking measures to ensure the necessary levels of protection and safeguards for the protection of the same, through the use of technically secure tools and channels and by entering into Standard Contractual Clauses, in accordance with applicable legislation.
7. Exercise of Rights.
The owner reminds users that Articles 15, 16, 17, 18, 20 and 21 of the European General Data Protection Regulation 2016/679, recognize numerous rights, including the right to: (a) to access the personal data concerning him/her; (b) to obtain the rectification and updating of the data, to request the restriction of the processing carried out on his/her data (including, where possible, the right to be forgotten and to erasure); (c) to object for legitimate purposes to the processing of the data, as well as to exercise his/her right to data portability; (d) to request to know the logic applied to the analyses and to request the modification of the outcomes of the study activities. Furthermore, the user, if he/she had given his/her free consent to the activities referred to in point 2 (d), (e) above, may at any time revoke his/her consent, even limited to specific contact methods. You may exercise these rights by contacting the Data Controller by writing to support@clayeditor.com.
Finally, we remind you that you can always lodge a complaint with the competent Control Authority (Data Protection Authority).
